                  <handDesc>
                     
                     <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
                        <seg type="script">Poor</seg>
                        <seg type="ink">Black; red.</seg>
                        <date>late 20th century.</date>
                        <seg type="rubrication">Nomina sacra; name of the donor; incipits of the
                           commemoration notices; the word salām; elements of the punctuation signs;
                           elements of Ethiopic numerals. 
 On the first page opening the
                           commemoration notices for a month, four groups of two lines are written
                           in red ink. The concluding formula, at the end of some months: ተፈጸመ፡
                           ወርኃ፡….</seg>
                     </handNote>
                  </handDesc>
                  <additions>
                     <list>
                        <item xml:id="a1">
                           <locus target="#170r">f. 170r</locus>
                           <desc>b: Za-ʾaqrabku māḥleta… “The song I am offering…” (concluding
                              prayer).</desc>
                           <quote xml:lang="gez">
                              <locus target="#170rb">170rb</locus>: ለዘአቅረብኩ፡ ማኅሌተ፡ አዘኪርየ፡…</quote>
                           <quote xml:lang="en"/>
                           <note> The note is written in the same hand. </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a2">
                           <locus target="#00"/>
                           <desc> </desc>
                           <desc>
                              <locus target="#170rc">170rc</locus>: Donation note.</desc>
                           <quote xml:lang="gez">
                              <locus target="#170rc">170rc</locus>: ዝመጽሐፈ፡ ስንክሳር፡ ዘወሀቦ፡ ሃለቃ፡ ገብረ[፡]
                              መድኅን። ወልደ[፡] ሐዋርያት፡ ለታቦቱ፡ ቅዱስ፡ ቂርቆስ፡ ወለታቦተ፡ ደብረ፡ መስቀል፡ ዑራ፡
                              ለ[sic]ጉለማከዳ፡… በ፲ወ፱፻፹ወ፪[?]ዓ፡ ም፡ በዘመነ፡ ቅዱስ፡ ማርቆስ፡ ወንጌላዊ፡ በቄስ፡ ገበዝ፡ ቀሺ፡
                              ወልደ[፡]  ማርያም፡ ተስፋ፡ ሚካኤል፡</quote>
                           <quote xml:lang="en"/>
                           <note> The note, written in the same hand, mentions haläqa Gabra Madḫǝn
                              Walda Ḥawāryāt as the one who donated the Ms. to the tabot of Qǝddus
                              Qirqos and of Dabra Masqal, in ʿUra Gulämakäda, in the year of mercy
                              1982, time of St Mark the Evangelist (= 1989/90 A.D.). The gabaz was
                              qäši Walda Māryām Tasfā Mikāʾel. </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e1">
                           <desc type="findingAid">Notes (written in the same hand, in red and black)
                              concerning the content of some entries are in the margins of fols.
                              57r, 58r, 116r, 168v.</desc>
                        </item>
                     </list>
                  </additions>
